            "answer_text": "You ask about \u201csound\u201d, not an electrical conversion to amplifier to speaker. So, any type of cone that has one small end that you hold to your ear and a large end aimed at the sound source can give your ear an amplified sound. If you hold small end to your mouth, and aim the large end at the point where you want your voice to be heard, you in effect amplify your voice. ",
